data.value: This function is functionally equivalent to calling binary_dilation with the number of iterations less than one: iterative dilation until the result does not change anymore.
The succession of an erosion and propagation inside the original image can be used instead of an
for deleting small objects while keeping the contours of larger objects untouched.
Binary image to be propagated inside
Structuring element used in the successive dilations. The output may depend on the structuring element, especially if
has several connex components. If no structuring element is provided, an element is generated with a squared connectivity equal to one.
Binary mask defining the region into which
Array of the same shape as input, into which the output is placed. By default, a new array is created.
Value at the border in the output array.
Placement of the filter, by default 0.

children.type_: int or tuple of ints, optional

data.value: Multidimensional binary propagation with the given structuring element.

signature.value: binary_propagation(input, structure=None, mask=None, output=None, border_value=0, origin=0)
